From: Andreas Herrmann <andreas.herrmann@caviumnetworks.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2015 12:21:09 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 126/184] MIPS: OCTEON: Provide sysmips call
 MIPS_CAVIUM_ARM_TIMER only for CONFIG_CAVIUM_OCTEON_SOC

Source: Cavium Networks, Inc.
MR: 00000
Type: Integration
Disposition: Merged from Octeon Tree
ChangeID: 59f4cb31d0e5a904e0e64098b23b8655ca054ba0
Description:

When building a paravirt kernel with CONFIG_CPU_CAVIUM_OCTEON=y the
build fails with

 arch/mips/built-in.o: In function `SYSC_sysmips':
 linux-octeon-sdk/arch/mips/kernel/syscall.c:242: undefined reference to `arm_timer'
 make[1]: *** [vmlinux] Error 1

because this function is only available if CONFIG_CAVIUM_OCTEON_SOC=y.

Signed-off-by: Andreas Herrmann <andreas.herrmann@caviumnetworks.com>
Signed-off-by: Corey Minyard <cminyard@mvista.com>
[Original patch taken from octeon-linux-kernel-patches-SDK-3.1.2-release]
Signed-off-by: Yanjiang Jin <yanjiang.jin@windriver.com>
---
 arch/mips/kernel/syscall.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/mips/kernel/syscall.c b/arch/mips/kernel/syscall.c
index dce4dcd..49dc743 100644
--- a/arch/mips/kernel/syscall.c
+++ b/arch/mips/kernel/syscall.c
@@ -238,9 +238,11 @@ SYSCALL_DEFINE3(sysmips, long, cmd, long, arg1, long, arg2)
 	case MIPS_CAVIUM_XKPHYS_WRITE:
 		return xkphys_usermem_write(arg1, arg2);
 
+#ifdef CONFIG_CAVIUM_OCTEON_SOC
 	case MIPS_CAVIUM_ARM_TIMER:
 		return arm_timer(arg1, arg2);
 #endif
+#endif
 
 	}
 
